1
00:00:05,682 --> 00:00:09,477
I'm Kogoro Mouri. A detective.

2
00:00:10,269 --> 00:00:14,190
Just as fish live wherever
there's an ocean...

3
00:00:14,273 --> 00:00:16,984
I find myself present
at murder scenes.

4
00:00:18,069 --> 00:00:19,320
It all started when...

5
00:00:19,404 --> 00:00:23,700
a bartender named Yuzuki Fukui,
who has a liking for me, asked for my help...

6
00:00:23,783 --> 00:00:27,954
and I came to the pool bar
where she works.

7
00:00:29,247 --> 00:00:31,416
Her request was this.
While on shift...

8
00:00:31,499 --> 00:00:34,085
she kept hearing a sound
like a champagne cork popping...

9
00:00:34,168 --> 00:00:38,881
and right after, the scent of yuzu
would drift through the air.

10
00:00:38,965 --> 00:00:41,342
She wanted me to solve
this strange little mystery.

11
00:00:42,385 --> 00:00:46,431
I was deep in thought
trying to work it out...

12
00:00:47,140 --> 00:00:51,436
when suddenly, one of the four people
sitting behind me...

13
00:00:51,894 --> 00:00:53,646
was murdered.

14
00:00:54,397 --> 00:00:58,025
The victim: Chikafumi Usuda, 51 years old.

15
00:00:58,109 --> 00:00:59,944
Apparently a department head
at some company.

16
00:01:00,737 --> 00:01:02,780
Cause of death: poison.

17
00:01:03,364 --> 00:01:06,117
It seems the killer coated the tip
of something sharp...

18
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:09,328
like an awl or ice pick...
with a nerve toxin...

19
00:01:09,412 --> 00:01:12,582
and drove it into the back
of the victim's neck.

20
00:01:12,999 --> 00:01:15,168
The suspects are three people
who came to celebrate...

21
00:01:15,251 --> 00:01:17,920
the victim's birthday
right here at this bar.

22
00:01:18,755 --> 00:01:20,590
The one who was made to buy
a billiard cue...

23
00:01:20,673 --> 00:01:22,091
as a birthday gift...

24
00:01:22,175 --> 00:01:25,219
Kensaku Hatsumura, 31 years old.

25
00:01:25,803 --> 00:01:28,431
The one made to buy
a set of darts...

26
00:01:28,514 --> 00:01:31,392
Monpei Kogure, 28 years old.

27
00:01:31,476 --> 00:01:34,604
And the one forced to buy
a rare Okino Yoko poster...

28
00:01:34,687 --> 00:01:36,647
along with a roll of camera film...

29
00:01:36,898 --> 00:01:39,567
Mika Kishiura, 30 years old.

30
00:01:40,401 --> 00:01:43,488
The most suspicious are Kogure,
who brought the darts...

31
00:01:43,905 --> 00:01:48,493
and Kishiura, who had been chipping
ice with an ice pick. But...

32
00:01:49,494 --> 00:01:51,913
Heh... alright then.

33
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:56,876
Let's say I won't be sleeping tonight
until this case is cracked.

34
00:01:59,295 --> 00:02:05,301
♪~

35
00:02:12,266 --> 00:02:15,853
Dark shadows and darker nights,
cut through by the light of deduction.

36
00:02:15,937 --> 00:02:19,524
A deduction show at the Blue Parrot,
unmasking the trick behind the hidden weapon.

37
00:02:19,857 --> 00:02:21,442
There is always only one truth.

38
00:02:21,526 --> 00:02:23,194
The body of a child, the mind of an adult.

39
00:02:23,277 --> 00:02:26,030
His name... Detective Conan!

40
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:56,746
~♪

41
00:03:57,870 --> 00:04:03,470
"Kogoro is at the Bar (Part 2)"

42
00:04:06,130 --> 00:04:07,256
What?

43
00:04:07,715 --> 00:04:10,843
No traces of poison were found?

44
00:04:11,552 --> 00:04:14,013
Not on the darts or
the ice pick either?

45
00:04:14,096 --> 00:04:16,766
That's right. According to forensics...

46
00:04:16,849 --> 00:04:20,227
there was no reaction to poison
or even blood.

47
00:04:20,311 --> 00:04:21,562
Hmm...

48
00:04:21,645 --> 00:04:25,524
You did search all three of them,
right?

49
00:04:25,608 --> 00:04:27,735
Yes. None of the three...

50
00:04:27,818 --> 00:04:30,404
had any vials or bags that could
have held a weapon or poison...

51
00:04:30,488 --> 00:04:31,989
on their person.

52
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:33,491
Hmm. I see.

53
00:04:34,241 --> 00:04:37,119
Unbelievable. No murder weapon...

54
00:04:37,203 --> 00:04:40,331
just like that pickpocket case
we had before.

55
00:04:40,414 --> 00:04:42,708
Oh, speaking of that case, Inspector...

56
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:45,961
did you ever mention it to Jodie?

57
00:04:46,253 --> 00:04:50,716
No. She's not directly involved.
No need to tell her.

58
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,802
I suppose not, but...

59
00:04:52,885 --> 00:04:55,888
Hey, Detective Takagi, what did
you mean by "it"?

60
00:04:55,971 --> 00:04:58,516
Oh? Well, you see...

61
00:04:58,599 --> 00:05:00,810
Takagi.
Yes sir.

62
00:05:00,893 --> 00:05:02,937
Let's sweep the bar one more time.

63
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:04,688
Right, understood.

64
00:05:21,956 --> 00:05:25,543
I wonder what Takagi meant by "it"...

65
00:05:25,918 --> 00:05:28,754
If there's something about that case
that stood out to me...

66
00:05:29,755 --> 00:05:31,924
it'd have to be that pregnant woman.

67
00:05:33,676 --> 00:05:36,220
Hm... what's this?

68
00:05:42,768 --> 00:05:44,436
(exhales) Hm?

69
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:47,064
Hey, Yuzuki.
Yeah?

70
00:05:48,023 --> 00:05:49,817
What is it, Conan?

71
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:53,028
What's that thing hanging
from the ceiling up there?

72
00:05:53,112 --> 00:05:56,615
Hm? Oh, that's just
a scrap of tinsel.

73
00:05:56,866 --> 00:05:58,701
A scrap of tinsel?

74
00:05:58,784 --> 00:06:02,204
Yeah. It was pinned up there
with a thumbtack, but...

75
00:06:02,288 --> 00:06:04,748
when I tried to take it down
it tore and part of it stayed up.

76
00:06:05,124 --> 00:06:07,334
We had a customer rent out
the whole place last week...

77
00:06:07,418 --> 00:06:09,753
for a private party.

78
00:06:10,296 --> 00:06:13,132
The ceiling up there is so dark
you can barely see it...

79
00:06:13,215 --> 00:06:17,219
so I just left it for now.
But can you actually tell it's there?

80
00:06:17,303 --> 00:06:21,432
Yeah. I'm always looking up
when I talk to grown-ups.

81
00:06:21,515 --> 00:06:22,558
Fair enough.

82
00:06:23,058 --> 00:06:27,605
Though all that looking up seems to mean
you're not watching where you step...

83
00:06:27,688 --> 00:06:28,689
little detective.

84
00:06:28,772 --> 00:06:30,733
Hm?
Look.

85
00:06:31,442 --> 00:06:35,279
There's gum stuck to the bottom
of his shoe.

86
00:06:36,322 --> 00:06:40,034
It wasn't there when he crouched down
near the body earlier...

87
00:06:40,117 --> 00:06:42,202
so where did he step in it?

88
00:06:42,828 --> 00:06:45,080
So? Did you find anything?

89
00:06:45,164 --> 00:06:46,999
Nothing.

90
00:06:47,082 --> 00:06:48,459
Hold it right there.
Hm?

91
00:06:48,792 --> 00:06:51,337
Looks like you stepped on
some evidence, mister.

92
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:53,172
What?!
Evidence?

93
00:06:53,255 --> 00:06:54,715
Takagi, get it.

94
00:06:54,798 --> 00:06:55,799
Right, yes sir.

95
00:06:58,385 --> 00:06:59,678
This is...

96
00:06:59,762 --> 00:07:03,265
It's not gum.
More like clay or putty.

97
00:07:04,016 --> 00:07:06,894
And there's an impression in it.

98
00:07:06,977 --> 00:07:07,978
What?

99
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:10,272
Letters, in reverse...

100
00:07:10,356 --> 00:07:13,734
four letters: E, P, D, H...

101
00:07:13,817 --> 00:07:16,779
and above them, some kind
of raised bump.

102
00:07:17,363 --> 00:07:21,075
If the impression reads "EPDH"
in reverse...

103
00:07:21,408 --> 00:07:24,411
then the original marking
would be "HDPE."

104
00:07:24,495 --> 00:07:27,790
High-density polyethylene.
A synthetic resin.

105
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:30,501
And the raised bump above it...

106
00:07:30,584 --> 00:07:34,088
means the clay was pressed against
something with a hollow or indent there.

107
00:07:34,338 --> 00:07:38,717
So it was probably stuck to the bottom
of that thing over there, but...

108
00:07:39,301 --> 00:07:42,930
why would there be clay
on the bottom of that?

109
00:07:43,222 --> 00:07:45,391
Ugh...
Hmm...

110
00:07:45,641 --> 00:07:48,519
I was supposed to be off the clock
by now, you know...

111
00:07:48,978 --> 00:07:52,731
I'd be in the bath humming to myself
by this point.

112
00:07:55,109 --> 00:07:56,402
The bath...

113
00:07:56,694 --> 00:07:57,695
(sharp inhale)

114
00:07:58,237 --> 00:08:00,990
That's it. That's how it was done.

115
00:08:01,657 --> 00:08:04,201
The murder weapon didn't vanish.

116
00:08:04,827 --> 00:08:09,289
The killer used that to launch it
clean off... a liftoff.

117
00:08:10,374 --> 00:08:12,876
Right out of any adult's line of sight.

118
00:08:15,629 --> 00:08:17,923
I've got it, Inspector.

119
00:08:18,590 --> 00:08:21,885
I know who murdered Chikafumi Usuda.

120
00:08:21,969 --> 00:08:23,053
What?

121
00:08:23,137 --> 00:08:24,805
Is that right?

122
00:08:24,888 --> 00:08:25,889
Yes.

123
00:08:26,265 --> 00:08:30,060
The killer is that customer who was
having a dispute with the victim.

124
00:08:30,144 --> 00:08:34,773
It looks like they've already left, but
if they came prepared with a poison needle...

125
00:08:34,857 --> 00:08:37,401
and walked out with it
after the murder...

126
00:08:37,484 --> 00:08:40,904
it would make sense that no weapon
was found inside the bar.

127
00:08:40,988 --> 00:08:42,156
Right, right.

128
00:08:42,239 --> 00:08:43,240
Hmm...

129
00:08:43,323 --> 00:08:46,535
...or so you might think.
But that's actually not the case.

130
00:08:46,618 --> 00:08:50,039
Excuse me? What exactly
are you trying to say?

131
00:08:50,122 --> 00:08:52,416
Ah... well, what I mean is...

132
00:08:52,499 --> 00:08:54,752
There he is. My other self.

133
00:08:55,294 --> 00:08:59,214
Any decent detective keeps a second voice
in their head...

134
00:08:59,298 --> 00:09:03,135
one that looks at their own reasoning
from the outside. But mine...

135
00:09:03,427 --> 00:09:06,263
always picks the worst possible moment
to show up.

136
00:09:06,346 --> 00:09:08,140
Just barging in like that.

137
00:09:08,724 --> 00:09:10,976
Since the Inspector and the others
seem to be hearing it too...

138
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:13,812
I must be saying it all out loud.
But I'm not even aware of it.

139
00:09:14,229 --> 00:09:16,648
Not even a little.

140
00:09:17,024 --> 00:09:21,195
It's like something I can't explain
has taken over my body.

141
00:09:22,154 --> 00:09:24,615
Well... that aside, the real problem is...

142
00:09:24,698 --> 00:09:28,452
the faint sting that shoots through
the back of my neck right after.

143
00:09:29,078 --> 00:09:30,204
(dart hits)
Ngh!

144
00:09:30,287 --> 00:09:32,081
Ah yes... there it is.

145
00:09:32,539 --> 00:09:36,460
And then, without warning, an overwhelming
wave of sleep crashes in.

146
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,879
I imagine it's the price
my brain pays...

147
00:09:38,962 --> 00:09:41,757
for running at full capacity
like that.

148
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,675
H... hey?

149
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:46,386
Here it comes. The usual.

150
00:09:46,386 --> 00:09:47,554
Lately... this sleep
actually feels kind of nice.

151
00:09:47,638 --> 00:09:49,515
And the reason for that is...

152
00:09:58,173 --> 00:10:00,759
Hey. Hey!

153
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:02,135
Hey!

154
00:10:02,219 --> 00:10:05,138
Mm? Ngh...

155
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,724
Hm?

156
00:10:07,808 --> 00:10:10,644
Are you awake?

157
00:10:10,727 --> 00:10:12,229
Mm... mhm...

158
00:10:12,771 --> 00:10:15,274
Everyone's already gone home.

159
00:10:15,357 --> 00:10:16,942
(yawns)

160
00:10:17,609 --> 00:10:19,403
So... the case?

161
00:10:19,486 --> 00:10:22,197
Seriously? What are you on about?

162
00:10:22,281 --> 00:10:25,909
You just wrapped up the whole
Sleeping Kogoro deduction show!

163
00:10:25,993 --> 00:10:30,539
Right... when I come back to my senses,
the case is always solved.

164
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:35,085
I suppose I pour every last bit of energy
into seeing through the truth...

165
00:10:35,168 --> 00:10:39,715
and laying it all out for everyone.
That's why I can't remember a thing.

166
00:10:40,257 --> 00:10:43,760
So the culprit really was that customer
who was fighting with him?

167
00:10:44,052 --> 00:10:47,723
What? I literally just said
there's no way some random customer...

168
00:10:47,806 --> 00:10:51,768
who happened to have a beef with the victim
would also show up with a poison needle.

169
00:10:51,852 --> 00:10:54,146
Oh... then could it be...

170
00:10:54,229 --> 00:10:56,899
one of those three coworkers
of the victim's...

171
00:10:56,982 --> 00:10:59,651
is the killer?

172
00:10:59,735 --> 00:11:00,944
Yes, exactly.

173
00:11:01,028 --> 00:11:03,071
No way.

174
00:11:03,322 --> 00:11:06,658
Sure, those three all had things
that could work as weapons, but...

175
00:11:06,742 --> 00:11:09,536
there wasn't a trace of poison
or blood on any of them.

176
00:11:11,163 --> 00:11:13,123
You doing okay?

177
00:11:13,206 --> 00:11:16,293
...You thought it was impossible too,
right, Yuzuki?

178
00:11:16,376 --> 00:11:17,377
Hm?

179
00:11:17,586 --> 00:11:20,380
Oh, I see. You were testing whether
I actually followed...

180
00:11:20,464 --> 00:11:23,550
your deduction properly.

181
00:11:23,634 --> 00:11:25,636
Ah... yeah, yeah, that's right.

182
00:11:25,969 --> 00:11:30,557
It made complete sense to me.
It all clicked perfectly.

183
00:11:30,641 --> 00:11:32,684
I never would have guessed
the killer used that method...

184
00:11:32,768 --> 00:11:35,479
to hide the murder weapon.

185
00:11:35,562 --> 00:11:37,981
That method?

186
00:11:38,398 --> 00:11:42,402
The experiment you had Conan help
demonstrate was a nice touch too.

187
00:11:42,861 --> 00:11:47,032
Takagi went and bought a film canister,
filled it about a third of the way with water...

188
00:11:47,115 --> 00:11:49,493
then took a bath bomb...

189
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:52,996
also picked up by Takagi, crushed it
down to roughly sugar-cube size...

190
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:57,000
and dropped it in...

191
00:11:57,417 --> 00:11:59,920
then sealed the lid on the canister...

192
00:12:00,379 --> 00:12:04,341
flipped it upside down and set it
lid-side down on the table...

193
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,594
and after about two and a half
to three minutes...

194
00:12:08,345 --> 00:12:09,721
Hm?

195
00:12:16,728 --> 00:12:18,355
...and that's how it works.

196
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:20,023
Whoa!

197
00:12:20,107 --> 00:12:22,609
We call this the film canister rocket.

198
00:12:23,151 --> 00:12:27,239
The bath bomb reacts with the water
and releases carbon dioxide gas...

199
00:12:27,572 --> 00:12:29,741
the gas builds up
inside the canister...

200
00:12:29,825 --> 00:12:34,371
and blows the lid open, launching the canister
high into the air like a rocket.

201
00:12:35,539 --> 00:12:38,208
Oh... it smells like yuzu.

202
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:40,293
Right. The killer...

203
00:12:40,377 --> 00:12:44,131
must have used a yuzu-scented bath bomb.

204
00:12:44,214 --> 00:12:47,801
Then that popping sound I heard
a few times before...

205
00:12:48,218 --> 00:12:51,304
The killer was doing test runs here.

206
00:12:51,972 --> 00:12:55,726
Practicing whether placing a weapon
on top of the canister...

207
00:12:56,018 --> 00:12:58,645
would be enough to drive it
into the ceiling.

208
00:12:58,937 --> 00:13:01,356
Wait, a weapon on top of it?

209
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:04,443
We're talking about something
shaped like an ice pick.

210
00:13:04,526 --> 00:13:07,654
That thing is heavy.
There's no way something like that would fly...

211
00:13:07,988 --> 00:13:09,906
The tip of a hard dart is detachable...

212
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:13,368
and weighs about 18 grams.

213
00:13:13,452 --> 00:13:15,704
Light enough to be launched
just fine.

214
00:13:16,329 --> 00:13:19,583
On top of that, the killer used clay
to fix the detached dart tip
to the bottom of the canister...

215
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:22,044
and used a rolled-up poster as a guide tube
to keep it aimed straight.

216
00:13:22,127 --> 00:13:26,423
That way, even if the launch
was slightly off...

217
00:13:27,090 --> 00:13:32,814
it would still reliably reach the ceiling.

218
00:13:34,273 --> 00:13:35,983
Any of that seem wrong to you?

219
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:41,188
The one who bought his own personal darts
as a birthday present for the victim...

220
00:13:42,606 --> 00:13:44,274
Monpei Kogure.

221
00:13:46,777 --> 00:13:51,281
You could have coated the dart tip
with poison in advance...

222
00:13:51,364 --> 00:13:53,408
and kept it loaded inside the canister.

223
00:13:53,784 --> 00:13:56,495
And this film canister rocket trick...

224
00:13:56,578 --> 00:13:58,747
could only have been set up
by someone standing near that poster...

225
00:13:58,830 --> 00:14:00,791
which was you.

226
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:05,253
Most likely, after the victim
had drunk himself into a stupor...

227
00:14:05,337 --> 00:14:08,507
you deliberately lost at billiards
and darts against the other two...

228
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:12,844
and slipped away to get
alone with the victim.

229
00:14:12,928 --> 00:14:15,013
Pretending to drape a jacket
over him or something...

230
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:19,768
you drove the poisoned dart tip
into the back of his neck.

231
00:14:20,185 --> 00:14:24,981
Then you removed the tip and swapped it
for a spare you'd already prepared.

232
00:14:25,065 --> 00:14:27,776
The one with the poison on it...

233
00:14:28,735 --> 00:14:30,362
you fixed to the bottom of the canister
with the clay...

234
00:14:30,445 --> 00:14:32,781
and hid it by tucking it
between your knees.

235
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:36,952
After that, all you had to do was
create a small distraction...

236
00:14:37,035 --> 00:14:40,789
and quietly set the film canister
rocket on the table.

237
00:14:40,872 --> 00:14:43,291
Something like...

238
00:14:43,959 --> 00:14:47,754
"Hey, doesn't that person over there
look like someone famous?"

239
00:14:47,838 --> 00:14:49,214
Something along those lines.

240
00:14:49,464 --> 00:14:53,176
Of course, only after ordering
champagne by the bottle.

241
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:54,678
Come to think of it, back then...

242
00:14:54,761 --> 00:14:57,931
Hey, what about that first champagne
we had?

243
00:14:58,014 --> 00:15:00,225
Yeah, that one was good.

244
00:15:00,308 --> 00:15:01,309
What do you think?

245
00:15:01,393 --> 00:15:02,936
Works for me.

246
00:15:03,019 --> 00:15:06,022
Excuse me, could we get
a bottle of champagne?

247
00:15:06,106 --> 00:15:08,817
Of course.
And three glasses too.

248
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:12,612
Wait, isn't that guy at the counter
Kogoro Mouri?

249
00:15:12,904 --> 00:15:15,323
No way! The famous detective?

250
00:15:15,407 --> 00:15:19,327
Hm? I feel like someone's watching me...

251
00:15:19,411 --> 00:15:20,871
Photo, get a photo!

252
00:15:20,954 --> 00:15:22,497
Probably just looks like him.

253
00:15:22,581 --> 00:15:25,667
Yeah, the real Mouri wouldn't be
sitting around drinking like this.

254
00:15:27,419 --> 00:15:28,503
To finish it off...

255
00:15:28,587 --> 00:15:32,382
he popped the champagne cork at almost
the exact same moment as the launch...

256
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:34,259
Ngh... hm?

257
00:15:34,342 --> 00:15:37,596
Man, this cork is seriously stuck.

258
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:40,390
Don't let it fly over here!

259
00:15:40,473 --> 00:15:41,933
Yeah yeah, I know.

260
00:15:42,017 --> 00:15:44,477
(straining)

261
00:15:46,646 --> 00:15:50,233
Then sprayed the champagne
all over the standing poster...

262
00:15:51,484 --> 00:15:55,197
which wiped away any bath bomb residue
left on the table after the launch.

263
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,824
Gone, just like that.

264
00:15:57,908 --> 00:16:00,285
The proof is in the poster itself.
The wet patch on it...

265
00:16:00,368 --> 00:16:01,369
Hm?

266
00:16:01,953 --> 00:16:04,372
should smell like yuzu.

267
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:08,376
It does.

268
00:16:08,668 --> 00:16:13,173
But that poster was bought
by Kishiura, wasn't it?

269
00:16:13,632 --> 00:16:15,091
The victim had apparently been pestering
people at the office about it...

270
00:16:15,175 --> 00:16:17,802
repeatedly.

271
00:16:17,886 --> 00:16:21,181
If she hadn't ended up buying it...

272
00:16:21,264 --> 00:16:24,684
he likely would have brought
his own as a backup.

273
00:16:25,352 --> 00:16:29,022
As for the darts, gift someone a dartboard
and it's easy to predict...

274
00:16:29,105 --> 00:16:31,358
they'll ask for arrows next.

275
00:16:31,441 --> 00:16:33,026
And knowing the victim would want
tons of photos taken...

276
00:16:33,109 --> 00:16:36,238
for some birthday blog...

277
00:16:36,321 --> 00:16:38,782
it's perfectly predictable she'd end up
buying camera film too.

278
00:16:38,865 --> 00:16:40,867
He had it all worked out.

279
00:16:41,534 --> 00:16:44,704
Either way, all of this
will be confirmed by...

280
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:52,128
the murder weapon lodged in that ceiling.

281
00:16:53,421 --> 00:16:56,007
Only someone who bought those darts
could have had...

282
00:16:56,091 --> 00:16:59,594
a matching spare dart tip on hand.

283
00:17:00,011 --> 00:17:03,181
But if it's just the tip lodged
in the ceiling...

284
00:17:03,265 --> 00:17:04,808
then the film canister that launched it...

285
00:17:05,141 --> 00:17:08,603
with clay still stuck to its bottom,
should have fallen back down.

286
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:11,439
Of course it did. But at that moment...

287
00:17:11,523 --> 00:17:14,234
champagne was splashing all over
the victim's precious poster...

288
00:17:14,317 --> 00:17:16,111
causing complete chaos.

289
00:17:16,695 --> 00:17:20,073
Even if it fell, everyone was scrambling
to wipe the table...

290
00:17:20,156 --> 00:17:23,118
so they would have just knocked it aside
without a second thought.

291
00:17:23,785 --> 00:17:27,330
As for the clay that came loose
when the canister hit the floor...

292
00:17:27,414 --> 00:17:30,083
that's what ended up getting stepped on.

293
00:17:30,166 --> 00:17:31,251
And that clay had...

294
00:17:31,334 --> 00:17:35,255
the letters "HDPE" pressed into it
backwards...

295
00:17:35,338 --> 00:17:39,634
because that marking is typically stamped
on the bottom of film canisters.

296
00:17:40,010 --> 00:17:44,347
Then what about the bath bomb pieces
left on the table?

297
00:17:44,431 --> 00:17:48,226
He probably dropped them
into his own beer glass.

298
00:17:48,310 --> 00:17:52,689
Beer already has bubbles, so a little
extra fizzing wouldn't draw any attention.

299
00:17:52,981 --> 00:17:55,567
His perfect crime...

300
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:58,486
foiled simply because the Sleeping Kogoro
happened to be here.

301
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:01,531
You could say his plan
went up in bubbles.

302
00:18:06,536 --> 00:18:09,706
Ha. Nice one.

303
00:18:09,789 --> 00:18:11,791
...You said that yourself, you know.

304
00:18:11,875 --> 00:18:13,209
Oh...

305
00:18:13,626 --> 00:18:16,880
I mean really...
after you solve a case...

306
00:18:16,963 --> 00:18:19,883
the Inspector did say
you remember nothing, but...

307
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,676
I didn't think he was serious.

308
00:18:22,052 --> 00:18:24,012
So you don't even remember the motive?

309
00:18:24,095 --> 00:18:27,766
That the victim had ruthlessly bullied
a coworker into taking their own life...

310
00:18:27,849 --> 00:18:31,186
and this was revenge for that?

311
00:18:31,269 --> 00:18:33,563
Ah... no. Not a thing.

312
00:18:33,938 --> 00:18:37,067
You were so incredibly cool though.

313
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:38,151
Hm?

314
00:18:38,234 --> 00:18:40,070
Now hold on.

315
00:18:40,153 --> 00:18:42,530
There's no way I remember
absolutely nothing.

316
00:18:42,614 --> 00:18:46,242
Maybe what I thought was
my "other self"...

317
00:18:46,659 --> 00:18:50,205
is actually the true me...

318
00:18:50,288 --> 00:18:53,291
slumbering deep within. Heheh...

319
00:18:54,459 --> 00:18:58,922
Sure. In my everyday life I conserve
my energy...

320
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:01,841
saving it all up
for the Sleeping Kogoro.

321
00:19:02,342 --> 00:19:05,470
Either way, it's all still me.

322
00:19:05,553 --> 00:19:07,430
All good!

323
00:19:07,514 --> 00:19:10,225
By the way... is Conan okay?

324
00:19:10,308 --> 00:19:13,269
Hm? Come to think of it,
where did that little four-eyes go?

325
00:19:13,937 --> 00:19:15,855
He just left without me?

326
00:19:15,939 --> 00:19:20,026
Yeah. He had a quick word with Takagi...

327
00:19:20,110 --> 00:19:22,112
then bolted out looking completely pale.

328
00:19:22,695 --> 00:19:24,572
What were they even talking about?

329
00:19:24,656 --> 00:19:27,409
I caught something about
a pickpocket.

330
00:19:27,951 --> 00:19:29,786
There's a suspense movie
he's been wanting to watch...

331
00:19:29,869 --> 00:19:34,290
that's airing on TV tonight.
Takagi told him about it.

332
00:19:34,707 --> 00:19:36,459
Wait, really? Why the rush then?

333
00:19:36,543 --> 00:19:40,088
Because it's a real thriller.

334
00:19:40,672 --> 00:19:43,883
Get it? A "thrill"-er! Ha ha ha ha!

335
00:19:43,967 --> 00:19:46,094
Nailed it again.

336
00:19:46,719 --> 00:19:52,725
♪~

337
00:21:00,793 --> 00:21:06,049
~♪

338
00:21:06,508 --> 00:21:09,761
(Conan breathing hard)

339
00:21:09,844 --> 00:21:11,846
Something's off about
the pickpocket victim?

340
00:21:11,930 --> 00:21:14,390
Yeah. Do you remember?

341
00:21:14,474 --> 00:21:18,520
One of the victims from that case,
a guy named Tohei Benzaki...

342
00:21:19,145 --> 00:21:22,482
Right. He was the one taken hostage
during the bank robbery...

343
00:21:22,565 --> 00:21:26,027
along with our teacher Jodie.

344
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:29,697
Exactly. And when his wife showed up
afterwards, she mentioned...

345
00:21:29,781 --> 00:21:32,116
that Jodie had her eyes and mouth
covered with tape...

346
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,910
by a fellow hostage.

347
00:21:34,369 --> 00:21:36,704
But apparently the robbers specifically
made sure...

348
00:21:36,788 --> 00:21:40,166
to pick someone who didn't know
any of the other hostages to do it.

349
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:42,585
Something about not trusting someone
to be thorough if they knew the person.

350
00:21:42,669 --> 00:21:43,753
What...?

351
00:21:44,712 --> 00:21:47,966
Alright. Next, anyone here
without a companion or someone they know...

352
00:21:48,049 --> 00:21:49,217
step forward.

353
00:21:52,679 --> 00:21:55,682
You lot. Come get this tape.

354
00:21:55,765 --> 00:21:58,851
Use it to cover the eyes and mouths
of everyone who's with someone...

355
00:21:59,102 --> 00:22:01,437
and tie their hands behind their backs.

356
00:22:01,896 --> 00:22:05,608
People go easy on their own.
Can't have that.

357
00:22:05,692 --> 00:22:06,901
Here.

358
00:22:07,318 --> 00:22:10,405
Don't worry, we'll take care
of you lot ourselves. Heh.

359
00:22:10,488 --> 00:22:11,614
(robber chuckles)

360
00:22:14,450 --> 00:22:15,994
(hostage whimpers)

361
00:22:27,547 --> 00:22:28,798
Um...

362
00:22:28,798 --> 00:22:29,798
Excuse me...

363
00:22:30,049 --> 00:22:32,051
Sorry, let me put this on.

364
00:22:32,135 --> 00:22:33,177
Hmm...

365
00:22:33,261 --> 00:22:37,974
If she said her husband Kirihei
was also a hostage in that incident...

366
00:22:38,057 --> 00:22:40,560
then none of it adds up.

367
00:22:41,019 --> 00:22:44,439
There's no way a pregnant woman would
go out of her way to deceive a robber...

368
00:22:44,522 --> 00:22:47,483
that's too reckless a gamble
for anyone to take.

369
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,653
So did you try
contacting that couple?

370
00:22:51,029 --> 00:22:55,825
Yeah... I went to his place
a number of times, but...

371
00:22:55,908 --> 00:22:58,036
he said he had absolutely no memory

372
00:22:58,119 --> 00:23:00,997
of being involved in
any pickpocket murder case.

373
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:04,000
He turned me away at the door.

374
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:08,338
On top of that, this Benzaki guy
is single, no wife...

375
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:11,633
and says he doesn't know
any pregnant woman either.

376
00:23:11,841 --> 00:23:14,010
I have no idea what's going on anymore.

377
00:23:14,093 --> 00:23:17,347
No way... no way...

378
00:23:18,014 --> 00:23:21,225
Morning sickness is a symptom
that appears in early pregnancy, right?

379
00:23:21,309 --> 00:23:25,188
Y... yeah, that's right.
I have poor eyesight, you see.

380
00:23:25,605 --> 00:23:27,106
Then could it be...

381
00:23:27,190 --> 00:23:31,486
the man with the burn next to you
back then, was he your boyfriend or...

382
00:23:31,903 --> 00:23:34,489
I spotted him a couple days before.

383
00:23:34,864 --> 00:23:35,990
No way...

384
00:23:44,666 --> 00:23:46,000
No way...

385
00:23:52,090 --> 00:23:55,718
Stay calm. It's okay. Still okay.

386
00:23:58,346 --> 00:24:00,640
And now she's alone with Ran.

387
00:24:00,723 --> 00:24:03,643
If she's going to slip up, it'll be here.

388
00:24:04,018 --> 00:24:05,728
(groaning)

389
00:24:08,940 --> 00:24:12,485
So all three of them
could have committed the crime.

390
00:24:12,568 --> 00:24:14,487
No.
(gasps)

391
00:24:16,028 --> 00:24:21,328
Next Conan:
"The Restroom Where Ran Also Collapsed (Part 1)"

392
00:24:37,428 --> 00:24:39,428
Next Conan's Hint:

393
00:24:39,428 --> 00:24:41,428
"Key to the basement"

394
00:24:41,619 --> 00:24:42,828
That tomboy's coming back again?

395
00:24:42,912 --> 00:24:44,580
Kogoro's getting less
and less screen time.

396
00:24:44,663 --> 00:24:46,540
Hey, Ran-neechan...
